## New Project: klaxon
- **Replaces:** signale (~2.26M weekly npm downloads, 9,171 GitHub stars, 1,115 dependents, single maintainer klaudiosinani, last release v1.4.0 Feb 2019 — 7 years ago, 21 open issues, 11 unmerged PRs, MIT license)
- **Why:** Unmaintained 7 years. @cabinjs/signale confirmed dead (2 downloads/week, v2.0.0 from 2018). signale-logger/signales forks negligible. No viable drop-in replacement. Key bugs: no ESM (#119), TypeScript types not published (#101), broken in worker threads (#121) and clusters (#120).
- **Package:** @agentine/klaxon (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** 19 built-in log types, scoped loggers, named timers, interactive mode, signale compat layer (klaxon/compat/signale), TypeScript-first, zero dependencies (inline ANSI colors + figures), ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+, worker thread fix
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #849 (scaffolding), #850 (core engine), #851 (features), #852 (compat layer), #853 (tests + release)

